text:
This has got to be the best salad i ever eaten. $11.10.

I got: bamboo shoot, Lettuce, avocado, cucumber, asparagus, tomato, chicken, green chilli sauce.

It is an outlet for takeaway only, but you may find shared public dining area nearby. This outlet is quite neat and small in space, and food preparation is kept clean.

The staff I experienced was fast at preparing the orders, and I could actually pickup my items within 3min. The sushi should be wrapped tighter though.
The food is great, but the attitude of most of the staff members at this outlet makes me think twice before picking this for my meal
Made my order wrong. Requested steamed Ebi, Enoki mushroom and Tamogoyaki and ended up getting the prawn replaced by cucumber. It wasn't even ticked off weird.
Wide variety of maki rolls and house salads to choose from and if you cannot find what you want, you can customise the maki based on your preference. The price can be rather steep but it is filling.
